  "texts": [
    "By automating the extraction of clinical features, NLP reduces the reliance on manual abstraction, enhances the accuracy of data extraction, and enables the conversion of unstructured data into structured formats for analysis [21,23,24].Recent advancements in large language models (LLMs), as a subdomain of NLP have shown promise in revolutionizing healthcare, with tasks ranging from analyzing biomedical data [25] to extraction of social determinants of health [26,27].",
    "These technologies, such as ChatGPT, offer opportunities to analyze vast amounts of data efficiently and identify patterns related to social determinants that influence health outcomes [26,28].",
    "LLMs provide contextual understanding, temporal reasoning, and adaptability to complex free-text data compared to rigid pattern-matching or other approaches, such as bagof-words [29][30][31].",
    "By leveraging these tools, researchers can better understand the complex interplay between social factors and health, leading to more targeted interventions and improved patient care.In this project, we aimed to assess the impact of stressful life events on CRC screening adherence using the logistic regression model and LLM to extract stressful events from the social history sections of clinical notes for patients at the Medical University of South Carolina (MUSC).",
    "MethodsThe study is a retrospective chart review using longitudinal EHR data."
  ],
